panels.text: "Libraries are maps into new territories, grand places of learning and wonder"

panels.title: Librarian-Overview
panels.text:
Query Librarian uses the power of Sumo Logic to look at Sumo Logic, to help you explore your data and your Sumo Logic environment.

The Librarian helps you see:

*  who is using data
* what data is used
* how the data is used 

so you can better answer questions such as "why?" and "what for?"

queries.queryString:
_index=sumologic_volume
| count by _SourceName,_SourceCategory
| sort by _count

_index=sumologic_audit
| count by _SourceName, _SourceCategory
| sort by _count

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count by analytics_tier, query_type
| sort by _count

| sort by _count

## This page shows the list of indices we use in the Query Librarian.

queries.queryString:

| sum(data_retrieved_bytes) as total_data_served
| int( total_data_served / 1G ) as total_gb_served
| fields total_gb_served

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count by query, retrieved_message_count, query_start_time, query_end_time
| sum(retrieved_message_count) as total_messages
| int(total_messages / 1000000) as total_messages

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| where query_type matches "Interactive*"
| parse regex field=query "\s?(?<_atom>\w+)\s?" multi
| count by _atom
| where !( _atom matches "_*" )
| where !( _atom matches "*_*" )
| where !( _atom matches "*__*" )
| where !( _atom matches /\d+/ ) 
| where !( _atom matches /\d+/ ) 
| where !( _atom matches /[A-Z].*/ )
| where !( _atom in ( "sumologic", "wikiurl", "wiki", "activityname", "documentation", "operator", "query", "logs", "https" ) ) 
| where !( length(_atom) < 2 ) 
| fields - _count
| concat ( "https://help.sumologic.com/Special:Search?query=", _atom, "++operator&type=wiki" ) as _wikiurl
| tourl(_wikiurl, _atom) as _docurl
| _atom as activityname
| _docurl as documentation
| fields activityname, documentation

panels.title: Documentation Methods
panels.text:
## Here, we are using the activity of the system to show both special fields and operators you can read more about. 
## We dynamically create a URL pointing to our help site:  https://help.sumologic.com

queries.queryString:
_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| parse regex field=query "\s?(?<_atom>\w+)\s?" multi
| count by _atom
| where _atom matches "_*"
| where !( _atom matches "*__*" )
| where !( length(_atom) < 3 )
| fields - _count
| concat ( "https://help.sumologic.com/Special:Search?query=", _atom, "++operator&type=wiki" ) as _wikiurl
| tourl(_wikiurl, _atom) as _docurl
| _atom as activityname
| _docurl as documentation
| fields activityname, documentation

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count by user_name

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| where user_name matches "{{target_user}}"
| count by user_name
| compare with timeshift 1d 3
| sort by _count

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query 
| where user_name matches "{{target_user}}"
| timeslice 15m 
| count by _timeslice 
| outlier _count window=5, threshold=1, consecutive=2, direction=+-

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| avg(execution_duration_ms) as average_duration
| average_duration / 1s as duration_sec
| fields duration_sec

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| execution_duration_ms / 1s as duration_in_seconds
| count as query_count by duration_in_seconds
| sort by duration_in_seconds

| where query contains("{{grep_target}}")
| count by query
| fields - _count

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count by query_type
| sort by _count

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count by query
| replace(query, "\n", "|") as my_query
| replace(my_query, " ", "|") as my_query
| parse regex field=my_query "(?<verb>\w+)\|" multi nodrop
| where !( isBlank(verb) )
| where !( verb matches "_*" )
| where !( verb matches "time_range" )
| lookup documentation from path://"/Library/Users/wschmidt@sumologic.com/Sumo_Logic_Librarian/SumoLogic-Documentation" on operator=verb
| fields query, verb, documentation
| where !( isBlank(documentation ) )
| tourl(documentation, verb) as doclink
| count by verb, doclink
| sort by _count
| limit 10

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| where query contains("{{grep_target}}")
| limit {{results_limit}}
| "{{my_location}}" as my_location
| urlencode(query) as query_urlencode
| toLong(queryStartTime()) as query_start
| toLong(queryEndTime()) as query_final
| concat("@", query_start, ",", query_final) as query_range
| tourl(concat("https://service.", "{{my_location}}", ".sumologic.com/ui/#/search/", query_range, "@", query_urlencode), "Run This Query!") as query_url
| count by query_url, my_location, query
| fields - _count
